## How to trigger

Save one of the payloads below to `/tmp/payload.json` and run:

```bash
curl -s -X POST "http://localhost:8005/qa/planner/api/v1/solver/trigger" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @/tmp/payload.json \
  | jq '.'
```

The response contains `job_id` and (after the solver finishes) an
eventual `plan_id`. Poll for completion:

```bash
JOB_ID=<from trigger response>
curl -s "http://localhost:8005/qa/planner/api/v1/solver/jobs/${JOB_ID}" \
  | jq '{status, plan_id, progress: .progress_history[-1]}'
```

Once `status: "COMPLETE"`, grab the `plan_id` from the same response.
Every read query below uses it:

```bash
PLAN_ID=<from jobs response>
```

If you prefer, list recent plans directly (reads go to 8003):

```bash
curl -s "http://localhost:8003/qa/ai/api/v1/planner-output/?user_id=javi_test&per_page=5" \
  | jq '.data[] | {output_id, plan_id, status, fetch_rt, fetch_ct, created_at}'
```

