When a resource has insufficient RT/CT source data AND it wasn't marked
replannable, the analyzer must surface a warning in the analysis
report.

**Fastest check (2026-04-18, stdout log):** grep the solver log for the
summary line added to `_analyze_ct_rt_compliance()`:

```bash
SOLVER_CTR=$(docker ps --filter name=cff-solver-qa --format '{{.ID}}')
docker logs $SOLVER_CTR --since 10m 2>&1 | grep -E "PhaseJ|ct_rt_compliance"
```

Expected for TC-10 (neither flag replannable):
