## Known limitations (to re-test after the initial green run)

1. **Priority-2 anchor refinement** is not implemented. RT/CT output
   timestamps use midnight fallback for all days except day 0 (which
   uses partition `last_shift_end`). A follow-up can walk the solved
   assignments in `_extract_rest_day_rows` to shift the anchor to the
   most recent demand end within 24h.
2. **Auto-free weekends in LC-05** remain excluded from the exposed
   `free_weekend_vars_dict`. If a weekend has no demand on Sat or Sun
   for anyone, LC-06 does not explicitly couple it. The monthly target
   still flexibly satisfies the quota on any 6 days.
3. **Resource-category awareness in targets.** Currently all resources
   in scope get the same 4/2/6 targets. If certain categories have
   different rest rules per CCT, a future patch would vary targets by
   resource category.
